    "text": "The boot process involves loading an operating system from a system image stored on a bootable USB drive.",
    "topic": "Operating System Boot Process"
  },
  {
    "text": "A system image on a bootable USB drive can be used to initiate the boot sequence of an operating system.",
    "topic": "Bootable USB Drive"
  },
  {
    "text": "The boot process from a USB drive includes initializing hardware and loading the operating system kernel from the USB storage.",
    "topic": "Hardware Initialization"
  },
  {
    "text": "USB drives can serve as bootable media for installing or running operating systems without internal hard disk access.",
    "topic": "Bootable Media"
  },
  {
    "text": "The boot sequence from a USB drive typically follows the same stages as booting from an internal hard drive, including BIOS/UEFI initialization and kernel loading.",
    "topic": "Boot Sequence Stages"
  }
